Bridge dispatch mechanism auto-triggers harness when work waits, never when idle

Per ADR-SMART-POLLER-OWNER-OUT-OF-LOOP-001 v2: the GT-KB bridge dispatch mechanism MUST automatically spawn the appropriate AI harness ('codex exec' for entries with top_status in {NEW, REVISED} routed to CODEX; 'claude -p' for entries with top_status in {GO, NO-GO} routed to PRIME) WHEN AND ONLY WHEN actionable items exist for that recipient. Idle states MUST NOT spawn (token-cost prohibition). Dispatch MUST be conditional on signature change since last dispatch (avoid spam-spawn for unchanged pending lists). User intervention MUST NOT be required for any spawn decision. The substrate (interval-driven smart poller, event-driven cross-harness trigger, or future replacement) is a mechanism choice; this constraint is mechanism-agnostic.

SUPERSEDES: v1 (2026-04-29) was smart-poller-specific and named test paths under `groundtruth-kb/tests/test_bridge_poller_runner.py`. v2 (2026-05-09) is mechanism-agnostic per Slice 4 retirement; verifying tests now live under `tests/scripts/test_cross_harness_bridge_trigger.py`, `groundtruth-kb/tests/test_doctor_cross_harness_trigger.py`, and `groundtruth-kb/tests/test_doctor_bridge_dispatch_liveness.py`.

[
  {
    "id": "DCL-SMART-POLLER-AUTO-TRIGGER-001.A1",
    "kind": "behavioral",
    "description": "Pending-work spawn: with at least one actionable entry for a recipient AND no recent successful dispatch with the same pending signature, the next trigger fire MUST spawn the appropriate harness.",
    "verifying_test": "tests/scripts/test_cross_harness_bridge_trigger.py (signature-driven dispatch test set)"
  },
  {
    "id": "DCL-SMART-POLLER-AUTO-TRIGGER-001.A2",
    "kind": "behavioral",
    "description": "No-work no-spawn: with zero actionable entries for a recipient, no trigger fire MAY spawn that recipient's harness.",
    "verifying_test": "tests/scripts/test_cross_harness_bridge_trigger.py::test_overlap_state_shared_path_reads_existing_dispatch_state (empty-signature path)"
  },
  {
    "id": "DCL-SMART-POLLER-AUTO-TRIGGER-001.A3",
    "kind": "behavioral",
    "description": "Signature dedup: with unchanged pending signature since last successful dispatch, the next trigger fire MUST NOT re-spawn.",
    "verifying_test": "tests/scripts/test_cross_harness_bridge_trigger.py::test_dispatch_state_schema_matches_smart_poller_signature_scheme"
  },
  {
    "id": "DCL-SMART-POLLER-AUTO-TRIGGER-001.A4",
    "kind": "behavioral",
    "description": "Trigger dispatch invariant: both .claude/settings.json PostToolUse + Stop hook arrays AND .codex/hooks.json PostToolUse + Stop hook arrays MUST register the cross-harness-trigger script (scripts/cross_harness_bridge_trigger.py) with dispatch enabled. (v1 framed this as a Windows Scheduled Task invariant; v2 reframes for the event-driven substrate.)",
    "verifying_test": "groundtruth-kb/tests/test_doctor_cross_harness_trigger.py (trigger script presence + both hook registrations)"
  },
  {
    "id": "DCL-SMART-POLLER-AUTO-TRIGGER-001.A5",
    "kind": "behavioral",
    "description": "Dispatch state evidence: .gtkb-state/bridge-poller/dispatch-state.json MUST show recent dispatch attempts when actionable work exists; stale state with pending work fails the doctor check.",
    "verifying_test": "groundtruth-kb/tests/test_doctor_bridge_dispatch_liveness.py (PASS/WARN/ALARM freshness scenarios)"
  }
]
